					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    An Erudite Wizard</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">H</a> | 
		            2/7/2000 3:44:50 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">As an erudite wizard you will need to get to higher lvls before you can actually do some damage, like all pure spellcasters, your first lvl spells ar pathetic. The first thing you should do is head to your guild hall (go to the fountain and there should be a teleporting stone ontop of it. step onto the stone then you will have teleported to the palace of erudin, your guld is somewhere in it)and give the note you start with to your guildmaster<BR>
<BR>
    . Then you receive your guild tunic(You might want to just sell it since its so low ac and sells for bout 2gp)If you do sell it, Then go find a vendor in your guild that sells lvl1 spells. The only on you want is speare of light. It is very useful since it summons a light source better than your starting candle, dont bother with the other spells just stick with these. Then you should go to qeynos, Sure tox forest has some low lvl monsters to kill but in qeynos they are a lot more common, not to mention there is no mist in qeynos. Go to the teleporter next to the one that teleports you to the palace, It teleports you to the docks, there is a person next to the teleporter. hail him and talk to him using all the highlighted words and he'll give u a note to deliver to qeynos, makes some good money for a newbie. at the docks, you should see a white craft with ski like things underneath, go onto it, It is not the real ship, it will deliver you to the big ship when it comes and just wait.Itll come. warning: Do Not jump of the boat until it has reached qeynos.<BR>
<BR>
      At qeynos deliver the letter and look, you just made yourself some quick cash! go to north qeynos and fight gnoll pups, bats, decaying skeletons and lrg rats( select them then press &quot;C&quot; and it'll tell you your chance of winning) outside the gates until you gain a few lvls.Also you might want to get a bind here. Ask high lvl people whether they will bind you for a small donation, or if you die you start back i erudin( You get bind at lvl 12) <BR>
      <BR>
      At lvl 4 go buy your spells at the wizard guild in qeynos.Put one training point into meditate to regain mana much faster. buy Shock of fire, Root, gate in this order.then go out and test your new spells. by now you should go to qeynos hills, a bit higher lvl monsters there. Becareful when fighting wolves or bears, There are these two NPC's, Cros treewind and Holly windstalker(non player character) that walk around killing anyone they see killing wolves or bears.<BR>
<BR>
     At lvl 7-8 go to blackburrow and join a good group. Hunt there, lots of loot and nice xp. Learn the several locations in BB And learn what you can fight and what u cant. And beware of trains: Huge bunches of monsters heading for the zone border after a person. oh yes i forgot, if you're in trouble ZONE,monsters cant follow you through the zone borders so use this to your advantage.Lvl 8 you get a whole new set of spells get shock of ice, lessser sheiding, fingers of fire, firebolt, column of frost also in that order. Hopefully you would have learnt some saffer parts of BB that you can rest at and some of the locations in bb such as the elite ledge and snake ledge, cammander room, snake pit. Go to the snake ledge and meditate(Med) till full mana. then to kill a snake do this: con(consider) it, cons white or blue kill it, red or yellow dont. Root then blast with all you got. it should die.<BR>
<BR>
     Lvl 12, go buy your new spells depending on what you want. You MUST get shock of lightning and halo of light, they are very useful. Try to find a group camping the elite ledge. Notice how much damage your spells are doing? Compare it to your lvl 1 spells. they are more mana efficient. Now see whats so nice about being a wizard? And it just keeps getting better. This is as far as i take u, do the rest on your own.<BR>
                        <BR>
                         GOOD LUCK!<BR>
<BR>
     
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
