			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OK, this guy gave some good information.  I have only one major point of contetion here.  The first rank spells are not, im my humble opinion, useless, particularly useful is the AOE ( area of effect spell ) numbing cold.  At 3rd lv you can pull two snakes or gnoll pups and cast numbing cold delivering 7pts of damage to everything around you.  I sometimes pulled 3 mobs and would deliver 21 pts per casting.  Also, Frost Bolt, has a long range for first lv, so combined with the fast casting speed of shock of frost you can get two hits in on a mob before you have to melee.  That adds up to about 12pts of damage or so.  <BR>
I recomend<BR>
1. numbing cold - for multiple pulls and fast lvs<BR>
2. Frost Bolt - for a long range pull<BR>
3. Shock of frost - to follow your Bolt pull<BR>
4. The light spell for sure if you are blind :)<BR>
5. Get them all that you can.  The mana is cheap and you'll want them to practice skill with at later levels.  Hope this helps.  <BR>
That guy was definetly right about getting out of tox forest and over to qeynos though.<BR>

